UID:TODO-065962DB-DBE7-486B-8A58-30F41CC32516
DTSTAMP:20260331T215203Z
SUMMARY:Write letter for Tapiwa
DESCRIPTION:The nomination package should include:\n1. The name of the facu
 lty member with whom the student will be\n   conducting research\; Harry B
 ermudez and Todd Emrick\n2. Why funding is not available for this student 
 during the summer\;\n   Tapiwa is a first-year graduate student in Polymer
  Science and\n   Engineering working on a new collaborative endeavor betwe
 en two\n   research groups.  While both Emrick and Bermudez have submitted
 \n   proposals to support Tapiwa\, and continue to do so\, currently there
 \n   is no funding available to cover the summer period.\n3. How the stude
 nt shows commitment to increasing equity and\n   representation in their d
 iscipline\; As a native African\, Tapiwa has\n   very visibly represented 
 the Polymer Science department as a\n   Senator in the Graduate Student Go
 vernment (GSG).  He has advocated\n   on behalf of all students\, notably 
 by working to increase the\n   minimum wage for Master's students.\n4. A d
 escription of the student's strengths\; Tapiwa has a warm and\n   outgoing
  personality\, always welcoming individuals in our community\n   by name.\
 n5. A copy of the student's CV.
CATEGORIES:AssocDH
SEQUENCE:1
PRIORITY:5
STATUS:NEEDS-ACTION
END:VTODO
